items.title: Bryce takes to basepaths, plays in sim game
items.summary: Bryce Harper took another major step in his rehab on Tuesday, participating in a simulated game that included running the bases and fielding ground balls, per Chelsea Janes of The Washington Post.

items.title: Big characters up for Personality of the Year Award
items.summary: The group of nominees for the Esurance MLB Award for Best Personality is a quality quintet that exudes hardball charm. Adrian Beltre, Nelson Cruz, Bryce Harper, Francisco Lindor and Yasiel Puig are among the game's best and brightest, and their endless quest to make the game as fun as possible has paid off for everyone.
